Why raw_training_data is still needed
employee_total_points is built from raw_training_data — if you delete raw, you lose the ability to:

Rebuild employee_total_points if something goes wrong
Answer future questions like "which service did Amandeep score highest in?"
Add new tables later like points breakdown by service or points by training type
Reprocess historical data if query logic changes

Think of it like this:
raw_training_data     = original Excel data in BigQuery (source of truth)
employee_total_points = a summary report built from it
wow_change            = another report built from the summary
Deleting raw_training_data would be like deleting the original Excel files after summarising them — you can never go back!
And as we calculated earlier, even with years of weekly data it costs essentially nothing to store. So keep it — it's your safety net. ✅
